## D. REST Endpoint Inventory (Reformatted)

**Base path:** `POST /resources/remote/{path}`  
**Content-Type:** `application/json` (both request and response)  
**Auth:** None  
**Single resource class:** `RemoteRestResource` (`@Path("remote")`)

### Proofing Endpoints — Summary

| # | Path | Service Method |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `POST /AssessDevicePlusEmailRisk` | `remoteProofingService.assessDevicePlusEmailRisk()` |
| 2 | `POST /CheckDevice` | `remoteProofingService.checkDevice()` |
| 3 | `POST /VerifyPhone` | `remoteProofingService.verifyPhone()` |
| 4 | `POST /ConfirmPasscode` | `remoteProofingService.confirmPasscode()` |
| 5 | `POST /RequestPasscode` | `remoteProofingService.requestPasscode()` |
| 6 | `POST /ResendLink` | `remoteProofingService.resendLink()` |
| 7 | `POST /ValidateLink` | `remoteProofingService.validateLink()` |

### Proofing Endpoints — Detailed Specifications

<details>
<summary><strong>AssessDevicePlusEmailRisk (#1)</strong></summary>

**Purpose:** Device + email risk assessment (LexisNexis bundled product). No `sponsorUserId` required — uses address hash as fallback.

**Key Inputs:**
- `sponsorCode`, `appCode`
- `firstName`, `lastName`, address fields
- `email` (optional)
- `profilingSessionID`, `webSessionID`

**Key Response Fields:**
- `reviewStatus` (PASS/REVIEW/REJECT)
- `reasonCode`
- `verified`

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>CheckDevice (#2)</strong></summary>

**Purpose:** Device reputation check only (LexisNexis). Requires `sponsorUserId`.

**Key Inputs:**
- `sponsorCode`, `sponsorId`
- `appCode`, `appId`
- `firstName`, `lastName`, address
- `mobilePhone`
- `profilingSessionID`

**Key Response Fields:**
- `reviewStatus`
- `reasonCode`
- `verified`

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>VerifyPhone (#3)</strong></summary>

**Purpose:** Phone verification + passcode/SMFA delivery. **Most complex endpoint.**

**Key Inputs:**
- All PII fields (name, address, DOB)
- `mobilePhone` (required)
- `birthDate` (required, format: MMddyyyy)
- `profilingSessionID`, `webSessionID`

**Key Response Fields:**
- `verified` (boolean)
- `transactionID` (vendor transaction)
- `reasonCode` (SuccessfulOTPDelivery, FailedPhoneVelocity, etc.)
- `passcodeSent`
- `kbaAttemptCount`

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>ConfirmPasscode (#4)</strong></summary>

**Purpose:** Validate OTP entered by user against vendor records.

**Key Inputs:**
- `sponsorCode`, `sponsorId`
- `customerUniqueID`
- `passcode` (numeric only)

**Key Response Fields:**
- `verified`
- `reasonCode` (PassedOTPConfirmation, FailedOTPConfirmation, etc.)
- `kbaAttemptCount`

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>RequestPasscode (#5)</strong></summary>

**Purpose:** Resend OTP to previously-verified phone.

**Key Inputs:**
- `sponsorCode`, `sponsorId`
- `customerUniqueID`

**Key Response Fields:**
- `passcodeSent`
- `transactionID`
- `reasonCode`

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>ResendLink (#6)</strong></summary>

**Purpose:** Resend Equifax SMFA link (DIT only).

**Key Inputs:**
- `sponsorCode`, `sponsorId`
- `customerUniqueID`

**Key Response Fields:**
- `passcodeSent`
- `transactionID`
- `reasonCode`

</details>

<details>
<summary><strong>ValidateLink (#7)</strong></summary>

**Purpose:** Check if user tapped the SMFA link (DIT only). Polls Equifax SMFA status.

**Key Inputs:**
- `sponsorCode`, `sponsorId`
- `customerUniqueID`

**Key Response Fields:**
- `verified`
- `sessionID`
- `reasonCode`

</details>

