## C. Technology / Configuration Inventory (Improved Layout)

### Core Technologies

| Technology | Version/Details |
|---|---|
| **Java** | 8+ (inferred from JJWT 0.10.5 + Gradle 8.1.1) |
| **App Server** | IBM WebSphere 9.x (`IBMRestServlet`, `ibm-web-bnd.xml`) |
| **Build Tool** | Gradle 8.1.1 (WAR plugin) |

### REST & Web Frameworks

| Framework | Details |
|---|---|
| **REST** | JAX-RS 2.1 via IBM `IBMRestServlet` + `JacksonJsonProvider` 2.15.2 |
| **Dependency Injection** | Spring 5.3.33 (`@Autowired`, `@Service`) |
| **JSON** | Jackson 2.15.2 + IBM JSON4J |

### Data & Transactions

| Layer | Details |
|---|---|
| **ORM** | EclipseLink (weaving=false), persistence unit `RemoteRestPUN` |
| **Datasource** | `ipsWebDS` (JNDI) |
| **Transactions** | JTA via `JtaTransactionManager` (WebSphere-managed) |

### Other

| Category | Value |
|---|---|
| **Logging** | Log4j2 2.17.1 via custom `CustomLogger` wrapper |
| **Security** | **None in code** — Network-level only |
| **Session** | **Completely stateless** — No `HttpSession` |
| **Config** | `ips.properties` — URLs, credentials, secrets |

### ⚠️ Critical: `ips.properties` Plaintext Credentials

- Experian JWT username/password (prod secrets included)
- Experian client ID + secret
- ThreatMetrix API keys
- SSA OAuth client IDs
- 30 Experian test user records with full PII

